WEBVTT

00:02:01.554 --> 00:02:04.757
<i>Space travel log 0968.</i>

00:02:05.325 --> 00:02:11.231
<i>It sounds good to call the bounty-hunting</i>
<i>job a "freelance" job...</i>

00:02:11.297 --> 00:02:15.702
<i>but all that means</i>
<i>is that we're self-employed.</i>

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:18.571
<i>When we have no jobs,</i>
<i>we have none at all.</i>

00:02:19.272 --> 00:02:21.474
<i>Well, that's all a part of our destiny...</i>

00:02:22.242 --> 00:02:24.277
<i>but it's troublesome</i>
<i>that we're out of money,</i>

00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:29.482
{\an8}<i>And so, we get urges</i>
<i>to make quick cash.</i>

00:02:34.888 --> 00:02:36.623
Any problem with using these?

00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:43.363
Evens!

00:02:44.831 --> 00:02:46.166
Evens, is it?

00:02:48.701 --> 00:02:49.936
No, odds after all!

00:02:54.274 --> 00:02:55.675
Odds, is it?

00:02:56.276 --> 00:02:57.944
Yeah odds.

00:03:01.481 --> 00:03:02.849
Double ace Even.

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:22.468
I can't eat any more

00:03:23.603 --> 00:03:27.574
Well, it would be easiest for me
if you paid up in cash.

00:03:28.641 --> 00:03:29.742
So, what'll it be?

00:03:32.545 --> 00:03:34.347
A man does not take back his word!

00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:43.856
That's why I told you not to do it

00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:18.524
<i>Humans were meant to work</i>
<i>and sweat for their money after all.</i>

00:04:18.958 --> 00:04:20.660
<i>Those that try to get rich quick...</i>

00:04:21.294 --> 00:04:24.497
<i>or live at the expense of others...</i>

00:04:24.797 --> 00:04:27.500
<i>all get divine retribution</i>
<i>somewhere along the way.</i>

00:04:27.567 --> 00:04:29.969
<i>That is the lesson.</i>

00:04:31.371 --> 00:04:32.538
<i>But one thing about humans</i>

00:04:32.605 --> 00:04:35.341
<i>is that they quickly forget</i>
<i>the lessons they just learned.</i>

00:04:37.377 --> 00:04:39.379
Damn it.

00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:46.519
There was a fridge way back here?

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:00.033
<i>"Survival of the fittest"</i>
<i>is the law of the land.</i>

00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:03.603
<i>To fool and to be fooled</i>
<i>is the reason we live.</i>

00:05:04.704 --> 00:05:07.573
<i>I've never had anything good</i>
<i>happen to me when I trust others.</i>

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:09.575
<i>That's the lesson.</i>

00:05:16.683 --> 00:05:17.817
How much did you swindle?

00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:20.753
Would you stop saying things
that would hurt my reputation?

00:05:20.820 --> 00:05:22.088
He lost on his own!

00:05:22.355 --> 00:05:24.590
Because he couldn't see
through this cheat?

00:05:27.694 --> 00:05:29.696
It's part of one's skill
to see through it.

00:05:29.762 --> 00:05:31.698
At least give his clothes back to him.

00:05:31.764 --> 00:05:33.066
I'll lend them to him.

00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:34.701
Greedy, aren't we?

00:05:35.001 --> 00:05:37.403
It's rough out there in the real world.

00:05:47.513 --> 00:05:48.748
Hey, what's up?

00:05:49.982 --> 00:05:51.684
Something bit me.

00:05:51.751 --> 00:05:53.352
What do you mean, "something"?

00:06:06.365 --> 00:06:07.900
It wasn't a rat!

00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:10.036
Look at this! This wound on my neck!

00:06:10.436 --> 00:06:11.370
Hey!

00:06:11.437 --> 00:06:13.906
This is silly. It was a waste
of time running over here.

00:06:13.973 --> 00:06:17.110
Spike! I was bitten around that fridge!

00:06:17.844 --> 00:06:18.911
Fridge?

00:06:19.812 --> 00:06:21.447
You have a clue?

00:06:23.382 --> 00:06:25.618
I'm sure there was something.

00:06:26.586 --> 00:06:27.887
Nope, can't remember.

00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:55.848
You sure this is gonna work?

00:06:55.915 --> 00:06:58.651
The only thing it doesn't work on
are myopia and cavities.

00:06:58.718 --> 00:07:00.887
-Then it works on athlete's foot?
-Of course.

00:07:01.687 --> 00:07:04.791
Don't you have something more
legit that would get rid of sores?

00:07:04.857 --> 00:07:05.758
That would be this.

00:07:07.860 --> 00:07:09.529
-That gets rid of sores?
-Yeah.

00:07:09.962 --> 00:07:12.865
Crush this, and you boil it
in three cups of water until

00:07:12.932 --> 00:07:15.201
the liquid simmers down
to 1 cup, and you drink it.

00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:19.906
Spike, isn't there something
more different?

00:07:19.972 --> 00:07:21.207
Oh, I got just the thing.

00:07:21.474 --> 00:07:22.608
Yeah, give me that.

00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:25.845
Give me what you had before.

00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:37.590
Hey I'm feeling a lot sicker now.

00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:39.826
Do I look pale?

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:42.094
You're pretty pale to begin with.

00:07:43.129 --> 00:07:45.665
What is this awful smell?

00:07:45.731 --> 00:07:48.601
-Herbal medicine.
-Herbal medicine? This?

00:07:49.068 --> 00:07:52.939
It smells like you just left a rag
that cleaned up spilt milk out to dry!

00:07:53.005 --> 00:07:56.209
I think it's more like rotten soybeans.

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:58.978
Knock it off!
I have to drink this, you know!

00:08:09.121 --> 00:08:10.022
Oh, brother.

00:08:10.590 --> 00:08:12.725
Hey, now, this goes too far for a joke.

00:08:33.713 --> 00:08:35.047
It was a rat, right?

00:08:35.114 --> 00:08:37.116
There's nothing to make a fuss about.

00:08:38.718 --> 00:08:39.752
Am I wrong?

00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:40.853
I have no clue.

00:08:41.287 --> 00:08:44.257
He seems to have gotten some poison
that's not in this database.

00:08:44.891 --> 00:08:47.226
Looking at similar poisons.

00:08:47.894 --> 00:08:49.228
{\an8}Cryptosporidium.

00:08:50.296 --> 00:08:51.230
That's not it.

00:08:52.298 --> 00:08:53.900
Cholera?

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:55.902
Nope

00:08:57.303 --> 00:08:58.704
Ebola virus?

00:08:59.305 --> 00:09:00.640
Nope.

00:09:01.107 --> 00:09:02.041
{\an8}Bifidobacterium?

00:09:03.109 --> 00:09:04.310
Not even close.

00:09:05.011 --> 00:09:06.312
What is it?

00:09:07.013 --> 00:09:08.281
Ein, you're being noisy.

00:09:08.915 --> 00:09:11.217
I can say for sure
that it wasn't an ordinary rat.

00:09:11.884 --> 00:09:13.119
Hey, keep it quiet.

00:09:13.586 --> 00:09:14.921
So, what is it?

00:09:15.121 --> 00:09:15.988
Well, it's...

00:09:16.122 --> 00:09:17.723
A mysterious space creature!

00:09:18.724 --> 00:09:21.994
Spooky! The attack
of a horrible space creature!

00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:26.165
Oh, yeah, there's that possibility.

00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:29.135
Yeah, right.

00:09:29.268 --> 00:09:30.636
Then what is it?

00:09:30.703 --> 00:09:32.638
It's not in the database.

00:09:32.705 --> 00:09:35.308
-Yeah.
-These base-pairs are weird, too.

00:09:35.575 --> 00:09:37.109
You think so?

00:09:37.176 --> 00:09:39.612
We've never seen symptoms
like this before either.

00:09:40.279 --> 00:09:42.882
Other than a space creature,
what is it? What is it?

00:09:43.816 --> 00:09:49.155
Well, perhaps something like
a rat went through a mutation...

00:09:49.221 --> 00:09:51.857
and evolved into
some mysterious creature

00:09:52.191 --> 00:09:55.127
and carried a mysterious poison.

00:09:55.194 --> 00:09:56.796
What's that about?

00:09:56.862 --> 00:09:59.999
That isn't too different from the
"mysterious space creature" theory!

00:10:00.066 --> 00:10:01.200
This is too silly.

00:10:02.802 --> 00:10:05.204
Aiya, what are we gonna do, Ein?

00:10:05.671 --> 00:10:07.073
It's a space creature!

00:10:09.141 --> 00:10:10.676
It's spooky!

00:10:45.277 --> 00:10:48.714
All right. This is made
to sense heat sources.

00:10:49.382 --> 00:10:52.785
It's usually used
to find bounties that are hiding.

00:10:53.819 --> 00:10:54.687
Can you see me?

00:11:02.061 --> 00:11:04.964
All right, I'm gonna test it,
so move just like I tell you.

00:11:06.265 --> 00:11:08.434
Ein! Where are you going?

00:11:08.701 --> 00:11:09.368
Hey, wait!

00:11:09.435 --> 00:11:10.436
Hey!

00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:15.975
That's weird. Is it broken?

00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:22.081
Was that response from you?

00:11:22.248 --> 00:11:25.885
That story you were telling, about some
mysterious creature or something.

00:11:25.951 --> 00:11:28.454
-Oh, yeah.
-What happens if you're bitten?

00:11:29.255 --> 00:11:33.225
I can't say for sure until we catch
the creature, but I'm going to guess...

00:11:34.026 --> 00:11:35.094
death?

00:11:36.796 --> 00:11:39.999
No, why did it have to be this way?

00:11:40.699 --> 00:11:42.868
I still have a lot to live for.

00:11:44.904 --> 00:11:47.773
I haven't committed any crimes.

00:11:48.174 --> 00:11:51.944
I'm still young and lively.

00:11:52.745 --> 00:11:53.446
Lively?

00:11:54.880 --> 00:11:57.016
Oh, poor little me!

00:11:58.117 --> 00:11:59.985
Hey, now, why are you getting into this?

00:12:24.243 --> 00:12:26.979
<i>August 6th. Skyday.</i>

00:12:27.046 --> 00:12:30.950
<i>Today, we will go look for the spooky,</i>
<i>mysterious space creature.</i>

00:12:32.051 --> 00:12:36.489
<i>Lesson, lesson if you see</i>
<i>a stranger, follow him!</i>

00:12:42.328 --> 00:12:43.395
Are you here?

00:12:43.896 --> 00:12:46.532
Are you here, Mr. Spooky Creature?

00:12:49.335 --> 00:12:50.469
Ed! Ein!

00:12:50.870 --> 00:12:53.239
Hey! This isn't hide-and-seek!

00:12:57.543 --> 00:13:01.046
Exploration, experimentation, exclamation.

00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:04.383
Lights shine bright in the many towns.

00:13:04.450 --> 00:13:08.521
I will come back alive.
I trust you, Ed.

00:13:18.797 --> 00:13:19.999
Ein!

00:13:20.399 --> 00:13:21.567
Are you in here?

00:13:22.168 --> 00:13:23.068
You're not in here?

00:13:23.335 --> 00:13:24.570
Answer me!

00:13:25.171 --> 00:13:26.138
Really...

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:42.321
Ein, Ed What happened?

00:13:56.202 --> 00:13:57.269
Ein!

00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:00.539
Hey, hang in there!

00:14:00.940 --> 00:14:02.107
Where's Ed?

00:14:02.308 --> 00:14:06.145
I can't believe it got you this easily.
You're a dog! Where are your instincts?!

00:14:55.261 --> 00:14:57.129
No choice. Guess I'm going in!

00:15:12.311 --> 00:15:15.014
{\an8}<i>Cruising down Route 66.</i>

00:15:15.214 --> 00:15:18.617
<i>Approximate cruising time left: 82 hours.</i>

00:15:20.085 --> 00:15:23.589
<i>From here, we will enter full autopilot.</i>

00:15:24.690 --> 00:15:28.294
<i>After passing the gate, this ship</i>
<i>will automatically land on Mars.</i>

00:15:30.029 --> 00:15:32.698
<i>The route cannot be changed</i>
<i>after confirmation.</i>

00:16:11.036 --> 00:16:13.172
Ed! You aren't here, are you? Hey!

00:16:20.579 --> 00:16:22.047
Did that thing get her, too?

00:16:55.114 --> 00:16:56.582
Don't surprise me!

00:17:06.492 --> 00:17:07.793
I've been waiting for you!

00:17:17.069 --> 00:17:17.736
Excellent!

00:17:58.310 --> 00:17:59.378
Come on, you slime!

00:18:04.216 --> 00:18:05.117
Got him!

00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:24.770
This thing seems familiar.

00:18:29.708 --> 00:18:31.443
I guess I should have eaten that.

00:18:32.211 --> 00:18:33.812
Oh, yeah, it should be in the fridge.

00:18:39.485 --> 00:18:42.187
<i>That was when I remembered</i>
<i>everything.</i>

00:18:43.288 --> 00:18:44.756
<i>It was, oh, one year ago.</i>

00:18:45.858 --> 00:18:49.795
<i>When I'd gotten a hold of a real lobster,</i>
<i>I hid it in the fridge in this stockroom.</i>

00:18:50.829 --> 00:18:53.599
<i>Just so nobody else would eat it.</i>

00:18:54.733 --> 00:18:58.303
<i>But I had forgotten about it,</i>
<i>and left it in there for a whole year.</i>

00:18:59.638 --> 00:19:02.441
<i>I wonder what it looks like in there now.</i>

00:20:04.469 --> 00:20:05.604
Shit!

00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:09.575
Damn it!

00:21:19.978 --> 00:21:23.849
<i>You shouldn't leave things in the fridge.</i>

00:21:26.318 --> 00:21:27.386
<i>That is the lesson.</i>

00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:44.569
Sweet bean roll!

00:21:49.975 --> 00:21:51.777
Can't eat anymore.

00:24:10.015 --> 00:24:13.051
<i>And so they all passed away.</i>

00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:18.156
<i>Everyone, it was brief,</i>
<i>but thanks for your support.</i>

00:24:18.790 --> 00:24:20.559
<i>This was the last episode.</i>

00:24:20.926 --> 00:24:22.661
<i>I hope they rest in peace.</i>

00:24:22.961 --> 00:24:24.095
<i>Amen.</i>

00:24:25.197 --> 00:24:28.200
<i>And starting next episode,</i>
<i>we bring you "Cowgirl Ed"!</i>

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:30.168
<i>I'm the main character!</i>

00:24:30.235 --> 00:24:31.169
Hey, wait a minute!

00:24:31.236 --> 00:24:32.971
What kind of selfish crap is that?!

00:24:33.038 --> 00:24:35.640
<i>Next episode: Jupiter Jazz, part 1.</i>

00:24:35.707 --> 00:24:37.108
<i>There really is another episode!</i>

